{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92db479a-bb72-4b10-a6fe-142da395f99b","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your `.csproj`\n\nAdd the MTP adapter and coverage packages:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.Engine\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <!-- TRX report support -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <!-- Code coverage -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nAlso add this property:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n    resultsFolder: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults'\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: always()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: always()\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | `dotnet test` (in-process) |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` + `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n| Publishing | Automatic | Explicit publish tasks (use `condition: always()`) |\n\nThe `condition: always()` on publish tasks ensures results are reported even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1cf8face-004f-40d2-b0ff-9ca5265a9478","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. This is a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":768,"requestId":"480A:FBA15:30D2026:3568A47:69FBE2F2"},"id":"c0796ffa-005f-44a8-8317-1ff43adef19d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:55:27.182Z","parentId":"24f15814-bab6-4207-bffe-0fbb3232cf8c"}
